Make me a hinge. Yes, sir.

999
01:27:23,600 --> 01:27:26,800
Keep going, you're doing well.

1000
01:27:26,900 --> 01:27:29,000
Says he's doing well.

1001
01:27:35,700 --> 01:27:38,400
Oh, that's very good.

1002
01:27:38,400 --> 01:27:42,400
But I'm a bit confused, and perhaps you can help me.

1003
01:27:42,500 --> 01:27:45,900
What I don't understand is that you've been working...

1004
01:27:46,000 --> 01:27:49,700
since I think, what, about six this morning?

1005
01:27:51,300 --> 01:27:55,700
Yet such a small pile of hinges.

1006
01:28:24,800 --> 01:28:27,700
Oh, Christ. May I try that, sir?

1007
01:28:27,700 --> 01:28:30,000
Check the angle-lever. Maybe it's bent.

1008
01:28:30,000 --> 01:28:33,500
No, no. You wouldn't hear a click if it was the angle-lever.

1009
01:28:33,600 --> 01:28:36,000
Maybe it's the pin. Maybe the pin shaft is greasy. Ja, come on.

1010
01:28:36,000 --> 01:28:39,100
What did I just say? Here.

1011
01:28:40,500 --> 01:28:44,100
Herr Kommandant,

1012
01:28:44,200 --> 01:28:48,700
I beg to report that my heap ofhinges was so unsatisfactory...

1013
01:28:48,800 --> 01:28:53,100
because the machines were being recalibrated this morning.

1014
01:28:53,200 --> 01:28:58,100
I w-was put on to shoveling coal.

1015
01:29:21,900 --> 01:29:24,000
Strange, huh?

1016
01:29:24,100 --> 01:29:26,000
Yeah.

1017
01:29:30,800 --> 01:29:34,000
Thank you, Muek.

1018
01:29:34,100 --> 01:29:38,000
Ah, Lisiek. Don't touch the leather, it's just been oiled.

1019
01:29:38,100 --> 01:29:39,800
Rottenfuehrer. Oh, for me?

1020
01:29:39,800 --> 01:29:43,500
Oh, thank you very much, Herr Direktor. Thank you. Herr Direktor!

1021
01:29:43,600 --> 01:29:46,100
Herr Direktor!

1022
01:29:48,700 --> 01:29:51,300
Herr Direktor!

1023
01:29:52,500 --> 01:29:54,500
He was making hinges slowly.

1024
01:29:54,600 --> 01:29:59,500
So the man can turn out a hinge in less than a minute. Why the long story? Hmm?

1025
01:30:28,600 --> 01:30:31,400
Thank you, sir. You're welcome.

1026
01:30:34,600 --> 01:30:38,600
Nobody knows who stole the chicken, hmm? Tell him about the chicken.

1027
01:30:38,600 --> 01:30:43,400
A man walks around with a chicken and nobody notices this.

1028
01:30:43,500 --> 01:30:46,000
Save yourselves.

1029
01:30:46,100 --> 01:30:48,500
Tell him about the chicken.

1030
01:31:04,200 --> 01:31:06,300
Still nobody knows.

1031
01:31:18,000 --> 01:31:21,800
It was you. You committed this crime.

1032
01:31:21,800 --> 01:31:24,200
No, sir. But you know who, though.

1033
01:31:24,300 --> 01:31:26,600
Yes. Who?

1034
01:31:26,700 --> 01:31:29,700
Him!

1035
01:31:33,200 --> 01:31:37,100
He's very gifted. Yeah, sure. Bring him over.

1036
01:31:39,900 --> 01:31:43,800
Yes, sir. Thank you.

1037
01:31:49,900 --> 01:31:52,800
Thank you again, Herr Direktor. You're welcome again.

1038
01:31:52,800 --> 01:31:56,600
It's an honor to work for such a great company. It's great to have you.

1039
01:31:56,700 --> 01:32:00,900
I promise to learn everything about enamelware production. That's great.

1040
01:32:13,400 --> 01:32:17,600
Hello? Miss Elsa Krause is here. I only need five minutes.

1041
01:32:17,600 --> 01:32:20,400
She wants to speak to the Herr Direktor.

1042
01:32:39,900 --> 01:32:42,100
Yes.

1043
01:32:46,300 --> 01:32:48,600
He won't see you.

1044
01:33:19,200 --> 01:33:21,300
Please, sit down.

1045
01:33:24,500 --> 01:33:27,400
Pernod? Cognac? Uh, no. No, thank you.

1046
01:33:28,600 --> 01:33:31,500
So, what can I do for you?

1047
01:33:35,500 --> 01:33:38,600
They say that no one dies here.

1048
01:33:38,600 --> 01:33:41,300
They say your factory is a haven.

1049
01:33:44,100 --> 01:33:46,400
They say you are good.

1050
01:33:49,400 --> 01:33:51,600
Who says that?

1051
01:33:51,700 --> 01:33:53,800
Everyone.

1052
01:34:00,200 --> 01:34:03,100
My name is Regina Perlman, not Elsa Krause.

1053
01:34:03,200 --> 01:34:06,400
I've been living in Krakow on false papers since the ghetto massacre.

1054
01:34:06,500 --> 01:34:08,000
My parents are in Plaszow.

1055
01:34:08,100 --> 01:34:12,600
Their names are Chana and Jakob Perlman.

1056
01:34:12,700 --> 01:34:16,500
They are older people. They are killing older people now in Plaszow.

1057
01:34:16,500 --> 01:34:20,500
They bury them up in the forest. Look...

1058
01:34:20,600 --> 01:34:23,500
I don't have any money.

1059
01:34:23,600 --> 01:34:26,500
I, I borrowed these clothes.

1060
01:34:29,200 --> 01:34:31,300
I'm begging you.

1061
01:34:31,400 --> 01:34:35,300
Please, please bring them here.

1062
01:34:35,400 --> 01:34:37,900
I don't do that.

1063
01:34:37,900 --> 01:34:41,900
You've been misled. I ask one thing:

1064
01:34:41,900 --> 01:34:45,200
whether or not a worker has certain skills.

1065
01:34:45,200 --> 01:34:48,100
My father is an importer, not a metalworker.

1066
01:34:48,200 --> 01:34:52,100
Such activities are illegal. You will not entrap me!

1067
01:34:52,200 --> 01:34:56,500
Cry, and I will have you arrested. I swear to God!

1068
01:35:06,200 --> 01:35:08,900
People die. It's a fact of life.

1069
01:35:09,000 --> 01:35:12,800
He wants to kill everybody? Great! What am I supposed to do about it?

1070
01:35:12,900 --> 01:35:15,600
Bring everybody over? Is that what you think?

1071
01:35:15,700 --> 01:35:18,600
Send them over to Schindler. Send them all!

1072
01:35:18,600 --> 01:35:22,300
His place is a haven, didn't you know? It's not a factory.

1073
01:35:22,400 --> 01:35:24,700
It's not an enterprise of any kind.

1074
01:35:24,700 --> 01:35:27,600
It's a haven for rabbis and orphans...

1075
01:35:27,700 --> 01:35:31,000
and people with no skills whatsoever!

1076
01:35:31,500 --> 01:35:35,800
You think I don't know what you're doing?

1077
01:35:35,800 --> 01:35:39,400
You're so quiet all the time. I know, I know!

1078
01:35:39,500 --> 01:35:42,400
Are you losing money? That's not the point!

1079
01:35:42,500 --> 01:35:46,400
What other point is-- It's dangerous! It's dangerous to me!

1080
01:35:50,500 --> 01:35:54,100
You have to understand. Goeth is under enormous pressure.

1081
01:35:54,200 --> 01:35:57,400
You have to think of it in his situation.

1082
01:35:57,500 --> 01:36:00,400
He's got this whole place to run.

1083
01:36:00,500 --> 01:36:03,400
He's responsible for everything here, all these people.

1084
01:36:03,500 --> 01:36:06,500
He's got a lot of things to worry about.

1085
01:36:06,500 --> 01:36:10,700
And he's got the war which brings out the worst in people.

1086
01:36:10,800 --> 01:36:14,200
Never the good, always the bad. Always the bad.

1087
01:36:16,500 --> 01:36:21,100
But in normal circumstances he wouldn't be like this. He'd be all right.

1088
01:36:21,200 --> 01:36:24,700
There'd just be the good aspects of him which--

1089
01:36:24,700 --> 01:36:28,400
He's a wonderful crook.

1090
01:36:28,500 --> 01:36:32,900
A man who loves good food, good wine, the ladies, making money--

1091
01:36:33,000 --> 01:36:35,300
Killing.

1092
01:36:35,300 --> 01:36:38,100
He can't enjoy it.

1093
01:36:38,200 --> 01:36:41,300
Bejski told me the other day, somebody escaped...

1094
01:36:41,400 --> 01:36:44,200
from a work detail outside the wire.

1095
01:36:44,200 --> 01:36:48,200
Goeth lined up everybody from the missing man's barracks.

1096
01:36:48,300 --> 01:36:52,400
He shot the man to the left of Bejski, the man to the right ofhim.

1097
01:36:52,400 --> 01:36:56,200
He walked down the line shooting every other man with the pistol.

1098
01:37:01,300 --> 01:37:03,800
Twenty-five.

1099
01:37:07,700 --> 01:37:11,400
What do you want me to do about it? Nothing, nothing.

1100
01:37:11,500 --> 01:37:13,800
We're just talking.

1101
01:37:25,500 --> 01:37:27,400
''Perlman.''

1102
01:37:29,100 --> 01:37:31,200
Perlman!

1103
01:37:31,200 --> 01:37:34,000
Husband and wife.

1104
01:37:34,100 --> 01:37:37,900
Jakob and Chana Perlman!

1105
01:37:51,100 --> 01:37:54,400
Have Goldberg bring them over.

1106
01:37:56,300 --> 01:37:59,700
Muetzen ab!

1107
01:37:59,800 --> 01:38:01,900
Appell abtreten!

1108
01:38:37,700 --> 01:38:41,700
## [ Drunken Singing In German ]

1109
01:38:49,700 --> 01:38:53,800
I'm sure this will be better than those rags, Lisiek.
